Class Complex

  • java.lang.Object
    • Complex
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable

    public class Complex
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable
    This is a class for Complex numbers. This class contains methods for basic complex number manipulations

      • rotate

        public Complex rotate(double Q,
                      Complex rotatept)
        This method is used to rotate a complex number on argand diagram around a point by an angle Q. First, the point of rotation is subtracted from complex number, then the complex number is rotated. Next the point of rotation is added back to the complex number.
        Parameters:
        Q - rotation angle in radians.
        rotatept - the point of rotation
        Returns:
        the rotated complex number.

      • root

        public Complex[] root(int n)
        This method is used to find nth root of a complex number. Static polar method is used to create a complex number with modulus r^(1/n) and argument ((Q+2kpi)/n).
        Parameters:
        n - index.
        Returns:
        nth roots of the complex number in an array.

      • rationalpow

        public Complex[] rationalpow(int m,
                             int n)
        This method is used to raise a complex number to a rational power m/n. First nth root is calculated using root method, then each root is raised to the power m using pow method.
        Parameters:
        m - numerator of index.
        n - denomator of index.
        Returns:
        an array of complex numbers raised to the power m/n.
